    <fr:title text="exponentiable object">exponentiable object</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> be an object in a category <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> such that all binary cartesian products with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> exist. We say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>exponentiable</html:em> when the product endofunctor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[-\times  E]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> has a right adjoint, which we shall write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E\Rightarrow -]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
